<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>That is my entire point</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Benign">Benign</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:59 p.m. 26/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> That is my entire point<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2095" TARGET=_self>No whining here</A> (Ice)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>If you can only play 4 hours a day and you die and waste 2 of it getting corpse and XP that is ok because YOU DIED!! The point is don't die. If you don't play as much as others you won't be as high level whether you die or not(UO friends thing doesn't come into play about death XP loss). Just because you only play half hour a day doesn't mean you should level as fast as someone who play 8 hours. Nor should you be able to adventure with them. But someone who plays 4 hours a day and doesn't die will level just as fast as someone who plays 8 hours and does die.

<P>While we are on the subject:So why don't we just grant everyone that plays less then 5 hours a week 5 levels. Just to help them catch up. Instead of less XP loss upon death lets give people more XP for monsters(sorry for the sarcasm).
<P>Changing the game to make it easier takes away from the challenge of the game no matter how often you play.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
